  FIX 2: Admin-Only Crew Management
  Started: Thu Jun 25 21:51:47 EDT 2026
══════════════════════════════════════════════════
Done. Here's a summary of everything that changed and where:

---

**Changes made — `index.html`**

| Location | What changed |
|---|---|
| `addMember()` (line 849) | Added `if(!isAdmin)return;` as first guard — blocks the action even if called programmatically |
| `delMember()` (line 854) | Same early-return guard added |
| Add-member input + button (lines 866–872) | Wrapped in `{isAdmin && (...)}` — hidden from non-admins entirely |
| Remove (trash) button per member card (line 893) | Wrapped in `{isAdmin && ...}` — hidden from non-admins entirely |

`isAdmin` (`trip.ownerId === me.id`) was already computed in `TripShell` and passed as a prop to `CrewTab`, so no new plumbing was needed. Non-admins still see the full crew list, cost breakdowns, emergency contact editing, and the Leave Trip button — only add/remove are restricted.

There's no real server-side permission layer in this project (the only backend route is `/api/config`); all writes go directly to Firestore. The function-level guards in `addMember`/`delMember` are the right defence-in-depth here — the UI hides the controls, and the functions refuse to act even if called directly.

